in a javascript web app, how do you save text to a local file
To save the text in JavaScript Web App to a local file on your computer, follow these steps: 
1. First, make sure that `FileSystem` API is supported by the browser or device where you are running this code. You can check if it's available using `navigator.webkitStorageInfo`. If not, add an event listener for when storage becomes available and save your text there instead of local file system:
```javascript
if (typeof window !== "undefined" && typeof navigator === 'object' && typeof navigator.webkitStorageInfo === 'function') {
  // Save the text to web storage here...
} else if (!window.FileSystem) {
  console.error("Web Storage is not supported.");
} else {
  window.addEventListener('storage', function(event, key){
    var file = event.target;

    // Save the text to local storage here...
  });
}
```
